Let $G_1 = (V_1, E_1)$ be a weakly reversible E-graph with its stoichiometric subspace $\mS_{G_1}$. Suppose an E-graph $G = (V, E)$, recall $\mJ (G_1,G)$, $\mD(G)$ and $\eJ(G_1)$ defined in Definitions~\ref{def:flux_realizable}, \ref{def:d0} and \ref{def:j0} respectively.

\begin{enumerate}[label=(\alph*)]
\item\label{part_a} Consider $\dK(G,G_1)$ from Definition~\ref{def:de_realizable}, then
\begin{equation} \label{eq:dim_kisg}
\begin{split} 
& \dim(\dK(G,G_1)) 
